    "Commentary Vol. 345": "Repentance was required of the Jews , as a Nation, for all the Blood of the Prophets which had been shed amongst: them, and for that Opposition they made to the true Interest and spiritual Kingdom of the promised Messiah; the Want of that Repentance proved their Destruction, which soon followed the Introduction of the New Testament State.\n1. A general and national Repentance.\n1. That natural Repentance is a Duty inferrible from the Law, without the Supposition of a Revelation of Gospel Grace.\n1.  Repentance was required of the  Jews, as a Nation, for all the\nBlood of the Prophets which had been shed amongst: them, and for\nthat Opposition they made to the true Interest and spiritual Kingdom\nof the promised Messiah; the Want of that Repentance proved their\nDestruction,  which  soon  followed  the  Introduction  of  the  New\nTestament State.\n1.  A general and national Repentance.\n1.  That natural Repentance is a Duty inferrible from the Law,\nwithout the Supposition of a Revelation of Gospel Grace.",
