    "Commentary Vol. 83": "But God came to Abimelech in a dream by night, etc.] Put a dream into his mind, by which he cautioned him against taking Sarah `[char_Sarah_Ref]` to be his wife; so careful was the Lord that no wrong should be done to such a godly and virtuous person, to which she was exposed through the 364 weakness of her husband. Aben Ezra wrongly interprets this of an angel, when it was God himself: and said unto him, behold, thou [art but] a dead man, for the woman which thou hast taken; that is, God would punish him with death, unless he restored the woman, whom he had taken, to her husband; not for any uncleanness he had committed with her, but for taking her without her free and full consent, and without inquiring more strictly into her relation to Abraham `[char_Abraham_Exo_17]`, and connection with him, and for his impure and unlawful desires after her, if persisted in: for she [is] a man\u2019s wife, or \u201cmarried to an husband\u201d f1200; and therefore it was unlawful in him to take her to be his wife.\nVer.",
