    "Dr. Peter S. Ruckman": "gives the ones on the east side of Jordan. \u201cKedesh in Galilee\u201d (vs. 7) is up near Lake Huleh. \u201cShechem\u201d was a town in Mt. Ephraim in the tribe of Manasseh (17:7). \u201cHebron\u201d was the town given to Caleb for his inheritance (14:13\u201315). \u201cThe mountain of Judah,\u201d in this case, is the mountain Caleb took from the Anakim (14:12). Something to note when it comes to Hebron as a city of refuge is the story of Joab slaying Abner in 2 Samuel\nverse 8 gives the ones on the east side of Jordan. \u201cKedesh in Galilee\u201d (vs. 7) is up near Lake Huleh. \u201cShechem\u201d was a town in Mt. Ephraim in the tribe of Manasseh (17:7). \u201cHebron\u201d was the town given to Caleb for his inheritance (14:13\u201315). \u201cThe mountain of Judah,\u201d in this case, is the mountain Caleb took from the Anakim (14:12). Something to note when it comes to Hebron as a city of refuge is the story of Joab slaying Abner in 2 Samuel",
    "Commentary Vol. 83": "Therefore Abimelech rose early in the morning, etc.] Awaking upon the dream, could sleep no more, his thoughts running upon what had been said to him by the Lord in it: wherefore as soon as it was light he rose from his bed, and called all his servants; his household servants, and particularly his courtiers and counsellors, who had advised him to take Sarah `[char_Sarah_Ref]` for his wife, and had been assisting in it: and told all those things in their ears: how that God appeared to him in a dream, and told him that Sarah `[char_Sarah_Ref]`, whom he had taken into his house, was another man\u2019s wife, and that if he did not immediately return her to her husband, he would die, and all that belonged to him: and the men were sore afraid; lest they should be struck with death; and perhaps they might call to mind the burning of Sodom and Gomorrah for their sins, they had lately heard of, and might fear that some such calamity would befall them.\nVer."
