    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And Abimelech said, behold, my whole land [is] before thee, etc.] Instead of bidding him be gone, and sending him away in haste out of his country, as the king of Egypt `[nation_Egypt_Ref]` did in a like case, he solicits his stay in it; and to encourage him to it, makes an offer of his whole kingdom to him, to choose which part of it he would to dwell in: 371 dwell where it pleaseth thee; if there was anyone part of it better than another, or more convenient for him, his family and his flocks, he was welcome to it.\nVer.",
