    "A New and Concise Bible Dictionary": "Hashupha. [Hashu'pha] Ancestor of some Nethinim who returned from exile. Neh. 7:\n18. See also JARED. Jeremai. [Jere'mai] One who had married a strange wife. Ezra 10:",
    "Dr. Peter S. Ruckman": "to the PAST tense so that the prophecy will have no future application: \u201cHAD pity.\u201d The same thing is done again in\n18. Keil and Pusey and Meyer don\u2019t like\n18. There will be physical changes in the topography of Mt. Zion which take place at the Advent (Zech. 14:4). These literal, physical changes are called \u201cFIGURATIVE\u201d by the Pulpit Commentary as no writer in it believed three-fourths of the Old Testament long enough to tie his shoelaces. \u201cSymmetrical\u201d and \u201chypallage\u201d are the tradesmen\u2019s terminology here (Vol. 13, p. 52) for getting the sucker\u2019s money. It is done just like A. T. Robertson used \u201ccohative\u201d (see Acts 3:8 and comments) to fool the chumps who are studying Greek.) Ezekiel 47:1\u201312 explains the matter much more faithfully and much easier (as is usually the case) by telling us that the Dead Sea will be purified after the Advent so that there will be no trouble with fresh water going from Jerusalem to Shittim, which is on the border between Moab and Israel (Num. 25:1; Micah 6:5). \u201c Egypt shall be a desolation, and Edom shall be a desolate wilderness\u201d (vs. 19). [See Obadiah 9\u201318 and comments.] \u201cFor the violence against the children of Judah, because they have shed innocent blood in their land\u201d (vs. 19). The judgment on the heathen near Jerusalem (Edorn and Egypt) takes two forms (see Zech. 14:1\u201314 and comments). Strangers will no longer \u201cpass through\u201d Jerusalem (vs. 17) in the Millennium because they will come there only for the purpose of worshipping (Isa. 2:1\u20135), exactly as the Ethiopian eunuch (Acts 8:27) and the Queen of Sheba came (2 Chron. 9:1\u201312). Dummelow refuses to believe the city of Shittim is an historical reference to the Biblical city; he then tells us that the \u201cfountain\u201d (vs. 18) is really just a \u201cSYMBOL of the Lord\u2019s presence.\u201d So was the paper he just wrote on. \u201c But Judah shall dwell for ever, and Jerusalem from generation to generation\u201d (vs. 20). [See Lev. 26:4\u201316 and Amos 9:15.] Since neither Calvin, Luther, Melanchthon, nor Pope Leo believed the verse was a reference to the literal, physical, political restoration of the Jews (see Luke 1:30\u201334 and Rom. 11:25) anymore than A. T. Robertson, J. G. Machen, or Hort believed it, every type of feinting, twisting, ducking, dodging, and sparring known to a professional heavy weight is resorted to by the \u201cmajority of you know whats\u201d when they hit these last two verses. \u201c For I WILL CLEANSE their blood...for the LORD DWELLETH IN ZION\u201d (vs. 21). Since this passage illuminates Romans 11:26\u201327 and Hebrews 8:8\u201312 in the New Testament, it is attacked with all the fury of Hell by Conservatives, Fundamentalists, Liberals, Catholics, and Atheists. In the NASV \u2014recommended by Lynchburg and BJU (same Greek text as Chicago University, Colgate, Rochester, and Union Theological Seminary)\u2014we find: God does not CLEANSE Israel, He merely \u201cavenges\u201d their blood ( NASV , Joel 3:21). This ancient slander on the Holy Spirit\u2019s words is found in the writings of Kimchi ( 1880 ) and Keil ( 1890 ), both of whom taught that Edom and Egypt in the passage were to be allegorized and that Jerusalem and Zion in the passage were to be allegorized and that the fountain and the waters (vs. 18) were to be allegorized (Ah, yes, Origen, ol\u2019 buddy! Still at it I see! And this time with Bob Jones University to back you up. You\u2019ve come a long way, baby .) Now where do you suppose this \u201cunique\u201d reading could have come from? I mean, since the fools that some of you take seriously are ALL in agreement on getting rid of Israel\u2019s cleansing (see the NEB, TEV, NRSV, RSV, ASV, ASV, Living Bible, International, Jerusalem, Common, and the brand NEW, NEW, NEW, NEWNEWNEWNEWNEW NEW Version!), where do you suppose they went to school to reach such a marvelous \u201cunanimity of opinion\u201d? We\u2019ll give you one guess. If you can\u2019t guess it in one guess, get out of the ministry. This is the reading of A.D.\nverse 18 to the PAST tense so that the prophecy will have no future application: \u201cHAD pity.\u201d The same thing is done again in\n18. Keil and Pusey and Meyer don\u2019t like",
